But you wouldn't take  
         advantage of a friend, 
         would you?

516
00:22:09,660 --> 00:22:13,146
You--you talked me             
 out of that place just so      
 you could get it yourself.

517
00:22:13,214 --> 00:22:14,715
No, i--i didn't talk you   
     out of anything.

518
00:22:14,782 --> 00:22:16,116
I talked you into      
         following your heart.

519
00:22:16,183 --> 00:22:17,984
You're a man        
            with a dream, sam.

520
00:22:18,052 --> 00:22:19,353
I envy you.

521
00:22:19,420 --> 00:22:20,787
But if it makes you 
            feel any better,

522
00:22:20,855 --> 00:22:22,673
i'm willing to          
        come to an arrangement.

523
00:22:22,675 --> 00:22:24,641
Oh, yeah?                  
            Yes, uh, let's see.

524
00:22:24,709 --> 00:22:27,344
Yes. You no longer  
            owe me a favor.

525
00:22:32,801 --> 00:22:34,701
Oh, uh, robin.

526
00:22:34,769 --> 00:22:36,303
I'm all set.               
     Let me just get my purse.

527
00:22:36,371 --> 00:22:37,388
Darling, you look lovely.

528
00:22:37,455 --> 00:22:39,105
I'll get miles to      
         bring the car around.

529
00:22:39,173 --> 00:22:41,407
And, um, oh,           
         that's for the drink.

530
00:22:49,416 --> 00:22:51,851
So, rebecca,                   
 tonight's the big night, huh?

